  "prompt": "I saw this guy that disappeared on me four months ago and he's acting like nothing ever happened. What should I do?",
  "response": "Running into someone who disappeared on you can be really frustrating and confusing, especially if they're acting like nothing happened. Here\u2019s how you might approach the situation:\n\n### 1. **Assess Your Feelings**\n   - Take a moment to reflect on how you feel about the situation. Are you hurt, angry, or indifferent? Understanding your emotions will help you decide how to respond.\n\n### 2. **Decide What You Want**\n   - Do you want closure, an explanation, or to let it go? Your goal will shape how you handle the interaction.\n\n### 3. **Address It Directly (If You Want)**\n   - If you feel comfortable, you can bring it up calmly. For example:\n     - \u201cHey, it\u2019s been a while. I was surprised when you stopped responding after we last talked. Is everything okay?\u201d\n   - This approach lets them know you noticed their behavior without being confrontational.\n\n### 4. **Set Boundaries**\n   - If they try to reinsert themselves into your life without addressing what happened, it\u2019s okay to set boundaries. You don\u2019t owe them your time or energy.\n\n### 5. **Let It Go (If It\u2019s Not Worth It)**\n   - If they\u2019re not offering a genuine explanation or apology, it might be best to move on. People who disappear often do so because they\u2019re not ready or willing to commit, and that\u2019s not a reflection of your worth.\n\n### 6. **Focus on Self-Care**\n   - Spend time with people who value and respect you. Surround yourself with positivity and focus on your own growth and happiness.\n\nUltimately, how you handle this situation depends on what feels right for you. You deserve to be treated with respect and honesty, so don\u2019t settle for less.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
